<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="614" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[163,1369,2810,3119]" pageId="17" pageNumber="614">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dollman" authorityYear="1909" box="[165,389,2929,2963]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zena">Lophuromys zena</taxonomicName>
was described as a full species distinct from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="True" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1047,1182,2929,2963]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">L. aquilus</taxonomicName>
based on its larger size, was later considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="True" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[827,958,2968,3002]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">L. aquilus</taxonomicName>
, and was finally incorporated into the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[290,522,3012,3041]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavopunctatus">L. flavopunctatus</taxonomicName>
species group. Molecular and morphometric analyses confirmed its species status. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[163,925,3085,3119]" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" type="distribution">
<caption box="[163,925,3085,3119]" inLine="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="614" targetBox="[2109,2113,896,917]" targetPageId="17">
